[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/two_club"]
[Student "S"]
{After NORTH's 2\C opening, SOUTH bids 2NT, showing a balanced hand of at least 8 points. SOUTH 
actually has 12 points, but the time to show the extra strength will be later.

NORTH's 3\C bid is Stayman, asking SOUTH for a 4-card Major. SOUTH mentions his \Ss and 
NORTH bids 4\S, showing a minimum 2\C opener with 4 \Ss.

Now SOUTH adds his 12 points to NORTH's 22 minimum and gets 34. He bids 6\S.}

