[Student "S"]
{EAST has 3 points, so she responds 2\D to WEST's opening 2\C bid, 
then bids 3\C as a second-negative when WEST bids 2\S.

However, when WEST then bids \Hs, EAST finds two more points 
and bids 4\H.}

